<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4147] Rust: protocol should accept transports with non-static lifetime</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4147</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently for Rust language support, all protocols only accept {{TTransport}}s with static lifetime. For instance:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;impl TCompactInputProtocol {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/// Create a `TCompactInputProtocol` that reads bytes from `transport`.
&lt;/span&gt;    pub fn &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;(transport: Rc&amp;lt;RefCell&amp;lt;Box&amp;lt;TTransport&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;) -&amp;gt; TCompactInputProtocol {
        TCompactInputProtocol {
            last_read_field_id: 0,
            read_field_id_stack: Vec::&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;(),
            pending_read_bool_value: None,
            transport: transport,
        }
    }
   ...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This poses an issue when user has the following custom defined TTransport:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// A read buffer piggy-backed on T: Read. Write is not supported.
&lt;/span&gt;pub struct ReadBuffer&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;a, T&amp;gt; where T: &apos;&lt;/span&gt;a + Read {
  data: &amp;amp;&apos;a mut T
}

impl&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;a, T: &apos;&lt;/span&gt;a + Read&amp;gt; ReadBuffer&amp;lt;&apos;a, T&amp;gt; {
  pub fn &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;(data: &amp;amp;&apos;a mut T) -&amp;gt; Self { Self { data: data } }
}

impl&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;a, T: &apos;&lt;/span&gt;a + Read&amp;gt; Read &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; ReadBuffer&amp;lt;&apos;a, T&amp;gt; {
  fn read(&amp;amp;mut self, buf: &amp;amp;mut [u8]) -&amp;gt; io::Result&amp;lt;usize&amp;gt; {
    let bytes_read = self.data.read(buf)?;
    Ok(bytes_read)
  }
}
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s better to change the protocols to accept &lt;tt&gt;Rc&amp;lt;RefCell&amp;lt;Box&amp;lt;TTransport + &apos;a&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
